## Early game

**Elara** on Jupiter (Survival, levels 15-20 in the Corpus Gas City tileset) is
an accessible Survival for newer players to rotate a few times: Neural Sensors
come from regular enemy drops here, so any Resource Drop Booster or
Resourceful Retriever you already have will help. If you'd rather not run an
endless mission, **Themisto** (Assassination, Alad V) offers an alternative —
each Raptor variant summoned during the fight has its own small chance to drop
a Neural Sensor.

## Mid & late game

**Cameria** on Jupiter (Dark Sector Survival, Steel Path) is the strongest
squad option once your gear can handle it: the Dark Sector's intrinsic +20%
resource drop chance stacks with the Steel Path resource-drop passive against
dense Corpus Gas City spawns. **Sinai** (Dark Sector Defense) on the same
planet is a close second if Cameria's matchmaking is inconvenient.

The Kuva Fortress node **Taveuni** is worth keeping in mind too — it lets a
squad farm Neural Sensors and Kuva in the same run once Kuva Liches are part
of the regular rotation.

